Mexico Stocks: Cemex, Empresas Ica, Grupo Mexico Shares Drop

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-12-08T22:36:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/mexico-stocks-cemex-empresas-ica-shares-drop-bolsa-gains.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC  index (MEXBOL)  fell 1.1 percent to 36,641.31.  Mexican stocks followed U.S. equities lower as the  European
Central Bank  damped speculation it would boost debt purchases.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO)  , the largest cement maker in the
Americas, dropped 4.7 percent to 6.54 pesos.  Empresas Ica SAB (ICA*) 
, the country’s biggest construction company, fell 3.7
percent to 18.09 pesos.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB)  , the country’s largest
mining company, fell 1.2 percent to 37.45 pesos. Copper futures
for March delivery fell as much as 2.2 percent in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  